### Describe the feature

I thought this was already the case in useAsyncData but after some issues in my project and finding this issue (https://github.com/nuxt/nuxt/issues/22622) it is clear this is not the case yet.

It would be great if we would have an option to integrate caching using useNuxtData in the useAsyncData itself. 
I have been able to implement this myself with a workaround like:

``
useAsyncData(`page-${id}`, async () => {
  const { data: cachedPage } = useNuxtData(`page-${id}`);
    return (
      cachedPage.value || (await getPage(id))
    );
})
``

Which works great, it's just a bit less clean.
The only issue is that if you would want to use the default refresh function provided by the useAsyncData composable this would not really refresh but just use the cache.

